The paper deals with deep learning applied to computational imaging, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep neural networks (DNNs) for solving inverse problems is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The training of DNNs is a central theme of the paper, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information theory (cs.IT) in the context of imaging systems. Finally, the use of DNNs for solving inverse problems is a topic of interest in neural networks (cs.NE).
